claim.claim-text:
28. A method for harvesting a vessel section, the method comprising the steps of: 
making a first incision at a point corresponding to a proximal end of the vessel section to be harvested; 
making a second incision at a point corresponding to a distal end of the vessel section; 
introducing a vessel support member into the vessel section to support the vessel section; 
attaching a proximal portion of the vessel section to the support member; 
severing the proximal end of the vessel; 
orienting a tubular cutting device coaxial with the support member; 
advancing the cutting device over the vessel section and along the support member to core out the vessel section and tissue adjoining the vessel section; 
severing the distal end of the vessel; and 
harvesting the cored-out vessel section and adjoining tissue.
